From beyond the grave, Gawker has revealed an unnerving truth about media consolidation: the chief executives of some of the world’s biggest companies get to decide what you watch, our media columnist @benyt writes.

name: nytimes
text:
Wildfires in 2020 took deadly aim at California’s oldest and most iconic trees: the giant sequoia, the Joshua tree and the coast redwood. 

The blackened wreckage sends a clear message: These trees are in the fight of their lives. https://t.co/ZfooZonDbA https://t.co/LVwYjJw6kh
